The paper deals with game theory and network algorithms, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), as the paper focuses on analyzing the price of anarchy and finding a Nash equilibrium in a game. The second likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes an algorithm for finding a NE and an allocation profile. The third likely category is cs.NE (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with network replication games. The fourth likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper proposes a distributed algorithm for finding an allocation profile. The fifth likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper deals with network games and their equilibrium properties.
